        <h1>leonardo da vinci, mona lisa, 1503–19</h1>
       
            painted between 1503 and 1517, da vinci’s alluring portrait has been dogged by two questions since the day it was made: who’s the subject and why is she smiling? a number of theories for the former have been proffered over the years: that she’s the wife of the florentine merchant francesco di bartolomeo del giocondo (ergo, the work’s alternative title, la gioconda); that she's leonardo’s mother. </p>
